name: WKError.Code
desc: Possible error values that WebKit APIs can return.

items.name: case unknown
items.desc: An error that indicates an unknown issue occurred.

items.name: case webContentProcessTerminated
items.desc: An error that indicates the web process that contains the content is no longer running.

items.name: case webViewInvalidated
items.desc: An error that indicates the web view was invalidated.

items.name: case javaScriptExceptionOccurred
items.desc: An error that indicates a JavaScript exception occurred.

items.name: case javaScriptResultTypeIsUnsupported
items.desc: An error that indicates the result of JavaScript execution could not be returned.

items.name: case contentRuleListStoreCompileFailed
items.desc: An error that indicates the compilation of a rule list failed.

items.name: case contentRuleListStoreLookUpFailed
items.desc: An error that indicates a content rule list data store didnâ€™t find a rule list with the specified identifier.

items.name: case contentRuleListStoreRemoveFailed
items.desc: An error that indicates a failure to remove a content rule list from the rule list data store object.

items.name: case contentRuleListStoreVersionMismatch
items.desc: An error that indicates the rule list version is outdated and cannot be read.

items.name: case attributedStringContentFailedToLoad
items.desc: An error that indicates the failure to navigate to web content from an attributed string.

items.name: case attributedStringContentLoadTimedOut
items.desc: An error that indicates a timeout occurred while trying to load web content from an attributed string.

items.name: case javaScriptInvalidFrameTarget
items.desc: An error that indicates your content referenced an invalid web frame.

items.name: case navigationAppBoundDomain
items.desc: An error that indicates navigation failed due to an app-bound domain restriction.

items.name: case javaScriptAppBoundDomain
items.desc: An error that indicates JavaScript execution failed due to an app-bound domain restriction.
